When viewing a list of filters (eihter on the dashboard in the "Saved Filters" portlet or on the "Manage Filters" page) the list should also display the project that the filters search in.

This is especialy interesting when your JIRA installation holds a lot of projects. When a user for instance want a filter for each project that the user is a developer on that shows his or hers issues that has to be done by the next version, then the filter has to be named something like: "My issues for the next version of PROJECTNAME". The project name has to be a part of the filter name so the user can tell them apart or just know which filter is for what project.

Special conditions: If the filter search all projects then the text should say something like "All" and maybe be in itallic font.

